    <releaseNotes>
    - New: Metadata download: Add two new sources for covers: Google Image Search and bigbooksearch.com.
    - New: Content server: Allow specifying a reestriction to use for the server when embedding it as a WSGI app.
    - New: Get Books: Add a plugin for the Koobe Polish book store
	- New: calibredb add_format: Add an option to not replace existing formats. Also pep8 compliance.
	- New: Allow restoring of the ORIGINAL_XXX format by right-clicking it in the book details panel
    - Fixed: AZW3 Input: Do not fail to identify JPEG images with 8BIM headers created with Adobe Photoshop.
    - Fixed: Amazon metadata download: Ignore Spanish edition entries when searching for a book on amazon.com
    - Fixed: TXT Input: When converting a txt file with a Byte Order Mark, remove the Byte Order Mark before further processing as it can cause the first line of the text to be mis-interpreted.
    - Fixed: Get Books: Fix searching for current book/title/author by right clicking the get books icon
	- Fixed: Get Books: Update nexto, gutenberg, and virtualo store plugins for website changes
	- Fixed: Amazon metadata download: When downloading from amazon.co.jp handle the 'Black curtain redirect' for adult titles.
	- Fixed: When extracting zip files do not allow maliciously created zip files to overwrite other files on the system
	- Fixed: RTF Input: Handle RTF files with invalid border style specifications
	- New News Source: Economia by Manish Bhattarai
	- New News Source: Universe Today by seird
	- New News Source: The Galaxy's Edge by Krittika Goyal
    - Improved News Source: The Escapist
    - Improved News Source: San Francisco Chronicle
	- Improved News Source: The Onion
	- Improved News Source: Fronda
	- Improved News Source: Tom's Hardware
	- Improved News Source: New Yorker
	- Improved News Source: Financial Times UK
	- Improved News Source: Business Week Magazine
	- Improved News Source: Victoria Times
	- Improved News Source: tvxs
	- Improved News Source: The Independent
    </releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
</package>
